  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    I am a Senior Research Engineer at the Center for Advanced Vehicular Systems (CAVS) and a Lecturer in the Department of Computer Science and Engineering at Mississippi State University. I earned a Ph.D. in Computer Science, a B.S. in Computer Science from UNC Pembroke, and an MBA with a focus on Project Management from Mississippi State University. My research advances off‑road autonomous systems, multi‑agent robotics, and precision field robotics for agricultural and defense applications. By integrating ecological simulation, machine learning, and AI, I work to improve autonomous navigation, enhance ground‑vehicle mobility forecasting, and ensure robust system deployment in complex, unstructured environments. I am committed to bridging the gap between simulation and real‑world operation, developing technologies that deliver reliable autonomy in GPS‑denied and dynamic terrains. As an educator and mentor, I lead interdisciplinary research projects and guide students in robotic systems development, fostering innovation at the intersection of autonomy, AI, and field robotics.
  </div>

